info.name: Interoperability System's API
info.description:
# Introduction

It supports the following requests:  
*Healthcheck (for admin)  
*ResetStations (for admin)  
*ResetVehicles(for admin)  
*ResetPasses (for admin)  
*PassesCost  
*PassesAnalysis  
*PassesPerStation  
*CostBy

The user can specify the data format from a url parameter "format". The supported formats for data are csv and json.

# Error Codes

*400:Bad request  
*402:No data  
*500:Internal server error

request.description: Checks end-to-end connectivity by attempting to connect to the database. Returns status.
Attempts to delete all pass records from database and reset administrator's password to "freepasses4all". Returns status.
Attempts to delete all station records from the database and initialize the station's table with given sample data. Returns success status.
Attempts to delete all vehicle records from the database and initialize the vehicle's table with given sample data. Returns status.

Takes stationID, dateFrom, dateTo as parameters. The date should be given as year month day (without gaps) and month and day in 2-digit form (e.g. 20210118). Returns all the passes recorded at the specified station and within the specified time period. In case of failure, it returns the corresponding error status code.

Takes op1ID, op2ID, dateFrom, dateTo as parameters. Returns all the passes from op2ID operator's vehicles (vehicles whose tags are issued by that operator) recorded at op1ID operator's stations. In case of failure it returns the corresponding error status code.

Takes op1ID, op2ID, dateFrom, dateTo as parameters. Returns the total cost and the count of passes of op2ID operator's vehicles at op1ID operator's stations. In case of failure it returns the corresponding error status code.

Takes opID, dateFrom, dateTo as parameters. Returns the total cost and the count of passes of every other operator's vehicles (vehicles whose tags are issued by that operator) at opID operator's stations. In case of failure it returns the corresponding error status code.
